https://blog.nikfp.com/how-to-install-and-set-up-neovim-on-windows

- Install Windows Terminal & always run as admin
- Install a nerd font https://www.nerdfonts.com/font-downloads and change to it in windows terminal
- Install chocolatey or scoop
- Install powershell core `choco install powershell-core`
- Install neovim `choco install neovim`
- Install git `choco install git`
- Install ripgrep for telescope plugin to work `choco install ripgrep`
- Install zig/mingw for treesitter to work `choco install zig` or `choco install mingw`
- Create a `init.lua` file in `AppData\Local\nvim\`
- Copy the following code to your `init.lua` file https://github.com/nvim-lua/kickstart.nvim/blob/master/init.lua



